===Noun===
'''bat''' (''plural:'' '''bats''')

#A small, [[nocturnal]], flying [[mammal]] of the order [[Chiroptera]], which navigates by means of [[echolocation]].
#A club made of wood or aluminium used for striking the ball in sports such as [[baseball]], [[softball]] and [[cricket]]. 
#A turn at hitting the ball with a bat in a game.
# {{vulgar}} A low whore: so called from moving out like bats in the dusk of the evening.
# {{two-up}} The piece of wood on which the [[spinner]] places the coins and then uses for throwing them.  (Reference: Sidney J. Baker, ''The Australian Language'', second edition, 1966, chapter XI section 3, page 242.)

